        "title": "Add QA evidence artifact output",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add a QA evidence artifact schema grouped by `test`, `mapping`, `execution`, and `result` so QA suite runs, live transport checks, Vitest, and Playwright proof can share one machine-readable artifact without forcing everything into scenario terminology.\n- Emit the canonical artifact as `qa-evidence.json`; existing run reports such as `qa-suite-summary.json`, `*-qa-report.md`, and observed-message artifacts remain separate outputs.\n- Keep taxonomy and mapping provenance out of the base evidence producer: evidence stores runnable-test identity, mapping relation IDs/refs, execution facts, artifacts, and result data; report/gate consumers join that through the checked-in taxonomy and mapping layers.\n- Treat evidence `profile` as an opaque mapping id in the artifact. The mapped runner/taxonomy stack validates runnable profile membership; the base evidence schema does not hardcode the profile list.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm docs:list`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/qa-lab/src/evidence-summary.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/cli.runtime.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/live-transports/slack/slack-live.runtime.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/live-transports/whatsapp/cli.runtime.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/mantis/run.runtime.test.ts test/scripts/mantis-build-telegram-evidence.test.ts test/scripts/rtt-harness.test.ts test/scripts/npm-telegram-rtt-driver.test.ts test/scripts/npm-telegram-live.test.ts`\n- `pnpm tsgo:extensions`\n- `node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 extensions/qa-lab/src/evidence-summary.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/evidence-summary.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/cli.runtime.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/mantis/run.runtime.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/mantis/run.runtime.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/live-transports/discord/discord-live.runtime.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/live-transports/slack/slack-live.runtime.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/live-transports/telegram/telegram-live.runtime.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/live-transports/whatsapp/whatsapp-live.runtime.ts scripts/lib/rtt-harness.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- retired evidence artifact filename and constant scan\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: QA Lab producers now write `qa-evidence.json` with evidence entries that can represent QA suite scenarios, live transport checks, Vitest tests, and Playwright tests.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw Codex worktree on macOS, with focused unit/schema tests and extension typecheck.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Ran the focused evidence, CLI, live transport, Mantis, RTT harness, and script tests through `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs`; ran `pnpm tsgo:extensions`; ran docs list; checked formatting and whitespace; scanned for the retired evidence artifact filename.\n\nEvidence after fix: Focused Vitest passed 9 files / 149 tests; `pnpm tsgo:extensions` passed; `git diff --check` passed; formatter check passed; no retired evidence artifact filename or filename constant references remain in the scanned source/docs/workflow/test paths.\n\nObserved result after fix: Evidence entries are grouped as `test`, `mapping`, `execution`, and `result`. Mapping coverage rows keep relation role plus surface/category IDs; refs are grouped under `mapping.refs`; execution contains provider/model, channel, runner, package source, environment, and artifact objects; result contains status, failure, and timing.\n\nWhat was not tested: No maturity or release gate was added or run, no channel-driver SDK lane was implemented, and no live Telegram provider lane was executed for this scoped schema/output-shape change.\n",
